  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Jamieson-Fausset-Brown Bible Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "CHAPTER 4",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Ac 4:1-13. Peter and John before the Samhedrim.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "1-12. the captain—of the Levitical guard.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "of the temple—annoyed at the disturbance created around it.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and the Sadducees—who \"say that there is no resurrection\" (Ac 23:8), irritated at the apostles \"preaching through (rather, 'in') Jesus the resurrection from the dead\"; for the resurrection of Christ, if a fact, effectually overthrew the Sadducean doctrine.",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
