          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "unto the next day: for it was now eventide",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] The Jews were not allowed to give judgment in the night, and their day ceased with the twelfth hour. It was already about the ninth hour when Peter and John were going up to the Temple (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 3:1",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), so that before the address of Peter and the arrest of him and John was completed it would be too late to enter on a judicial enquiry. The Rabbis founded the prohibition on ",
        "children": []
      },
